	"name": "Anchor Man",
	"tooltip": "Ultra-disciplined holding midfielder who never leaves position in front of the defense.",
	"description": "The Anchor Man is football's ultimate positional purist - a defensive midfielder who sacrifices mobility for structural perfection. With exceptional position maintenance discipline and minimal roaming range, this role provides an immovable shield in front of the defense. The Anchor prioritizes safe, simple distribution over creative passing, offering outlets under pressure but rarely attempting risky through balls or switches. Minimal attacking involvement means extremely low penalty box invasion and forward runs, instead focusing on close support and maintaining defensive shape. Exceptional spatial awareness and covering frequency ensure defensive balance is never compromised. The role excels at intercepting passes through cover shadow priority and second ball anticipation, preferring intelligent positioning over aggressive tackling. Works best in systems requiring a dedicated positional anchor, allowing more adventurous teammates to push forward with confidence. Think Claude Makélélé, Sergio Busquets, or Fabinho - players who make the complex look simple through perfect positioning and game-reading ability.",
